From: Andrea Righi <arighi@nvidia.com>
Subject: [PATCH] sched_ext: Add SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE enqueue flag (7.0.11 backport)

Backport of arighi for-7.2 commit aee94395c1f7e5e6414db223acc8d672603fed93
("sched_ext: Add SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE enqueue flag") to the CachyOS 7.0.11
tree. The upstream patch does not apply there because its context depends
on SCX_ENQ_IMMED and scx_vet_enq_flags(), which only exist in for-7.2.

Backport deltas vs upstream (behavior identical):
 - 7.0.11's local_dsq_post_enq() has no scx_sched *sch param; use the
   file-scope scx_root directly (same pattern as yield_to_task_scx()).
 - No scx_vet_enq_flags() on 7.0.11; the non-local-DSQ validation goes at
   the top of scx_dsq_insert_commit(), which every dsq-insert kfunc
   (FIFO + vtime, v1 + v2) routes through.
 - Same bit value as upstream: 1LLU << 34 (free on 7.0.11; bit 33/IMMED
   does not exist here). Userspace resolves the bit from kernel BTF at
   runtime, so the value only needs to match this kernel's own enum.
 - tools/sched_ext autogen header hunks dropped: scx_cake resolves the
   enum via scx_utils::compat::read_enum() from booted-kernel BTF.

When inserting a task into a local DSQ, a scheduler often wants to wake
the target CPU if it is idle. Currently, this requires a separate
scx_bpf_kick_cpu() call after the insert.

Add SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE, which can be set in @enq_flags when inserting
into a local DSQ. After the task is successfully inserted, the CPU
owning that local DSQ is kicked as if scx_bpf_kick_cpu() was called with
SCX_KICK_IDLE, folding the two operations into one.

The flag is only valid on local DSQs; using it on a non-local DSQ
triggers an scx_error().

Signed-off-by: Andrea Righi <arighi@nvidia.com>
[backported to cachyos-7.0.11 by Paul Reitz]
---
--- a/kernel/sched/ext.c	2026-06-10 09:21:30.394434947 -0500
+++ b/kernel/sched/ext.c	2026-06-10 09:22:54.000797724 -0500
@@ -1004,6 +1004,9 @@ static void local_dsq_post_enq(struct sc
 	if (rq->scx.flags & SCX_RQ_IN_BALANCE)
 		return;
 
+	if (enq_flags & SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE)
+		scx_kick_cpu(scx_root, cpu_of(rq), SCX_KICK_IDLE);
+
 	if ((enq_flags & SCX_ENQ_PREEMPT) && p != rq->curr &&
 	    rq->curr->sched_class == &ext_sched_class) {
 		rq->curr->scx.slice = 0;
@@ -5923,6 +5926,13 @@ static void scx_dsq_insert_commit(struct
 {
 	struct scx_dsp_ctx *dspc = this_cpu_ptr(scx_dsp_ctx);
 	struct task_struct *ddsp_task;
+	bool is_local = dsq_id == SCX_DSQ_LOCAL ||
+		(dsq_id & SCX_DSQ_LOCAL_ON) == SCX_DSQ_LOCAL_ON;
+
+	if (unlikely((enq_flags & SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE) && !is_local)) {
+		scx_error(sch, "SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE on a non-local DSQ 0x%llx", dsq_id);
+		return;
+	}
 
 	ddsp_task = __this_cpu_read(direct_dispatch_task);
 	if (ddsp_task) {
--- a/kernel/sched/ext_internal.h	2026-06-10 09:21:30.394754738 -0500
+++ b/kernel/sched/ext_internal.h	2026-06-10 09:21:54.282042735 -0500
@@ -942,6 +942,13 @@ enum scx_enq_flags {
 	SCX_ENQ_PREEMPT		= 1LLU << 32,
 
 	/*
+	 * Only allowed on local DSQs. After successfully inserting the task
+	 * into a local DSQ, kick the CPU owning that local DSQ as if
+	 * scx_bpf_kick_cpu() was called with %SCX_KICK_IDLE.
+	 */
+	SCX_ENQ_KICK_IDLE	= 1LLU << 34,
+
+	/*
 	 * The task being enqueued was previously enqueued on the current CPU's
 	 * %SCX_DSQ_LOCAL, but was removed from it in a call to the
 	 * scx_bpf_reenqueue_local() kfunc. If scx_bpf_reenqueue_local() was
